<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06257084 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06257084 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Two white extremists pleaded guilty in Durban, South Africa on Thursday tomurdering seven blacks in a bus ambush they said was meant to &quot;send a message&quot;to the black community. David Petrus Botha and Adriaan Smuts maintain theiractions were politically motivated and they should not be punished. OnWednesday, the two ended a 24-day hunger strike in protest of the trial afterfailing to persuade the judge to drop the case.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  S. AFRICAN EXTREMISTS ENTER GUILTY PLEAS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Foreign News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910913  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  18A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  78  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, September 13, 199100257084,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>